Introduction

Nayoung (나영) is a South Korean singer and actress under Goodman Story Entertainment. She is a former member of the girl group gugudan, its second sub-unit gugudan SEMINA, and a former member of the project girl group Sunny Girls.

Nayoung was first known for appearing and competing in the hit survival show Produce 101 in 2016 where she ranked 14th.

Nayoung debuted as a member of gugudan on June 28, 2016, with their EP "Act. 1 The Little Mermaid". On November 27, she debuted as a member of Inkigayo's project girl group Sunny Girls, which also included Eunha, Cheng Xiao, YooA, and Nancy.

Nayoung debuted as a member of gugudan's second sub-unit, gugudan SEMINA, on July 10, 2018 with their first and only single album "Semina".

gugudan disbanded on December 31, 2020.

On January 3, 2022, Nayoung signed an exclusive contract with Goodman Story Entertainment, where she will be promoting as an actress.
